page.title: 11Woodland
page.content: There is a lot of woodland in the surrounding countryside which is mostly{coniferous}and many wild animals like{rabbits and deer}live there. There is Lady Mary's Wood,Bogle Wood,Heggie's Muir Wood,The Wilderness and Greenrig Wood all within short distance of the village. The woods are mostly of{pine}with a few{ash and chestnut.}There are many trees on either bank of the River Eden which flows through the village. Most of the farmers who have woods on their land breed{pheasants}for game hunting.
